      "lineNbr": 91,
      "author": {
        "id": 1157909
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-31T22:50:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I see BatchCreateInvocationsRequest has a top-level RequestId field, but each CreateInvocationRequest also has a RequestId field. If we send a batch with an empty top-level RequestId but fill in per-request RequestIds, will it dedupe each invocation correctly?\n\nI don\u0027t think so. The per-request RequestId is supposed to be empty or the same as the top-level request id (http://shortn/_4LDVIPYyws).",
      "parentUuid": "f32e3727_296620f2",
      "revId": "ae81b31b939260bb8b6d9983061b0f0fa1c4460e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
